5:
Wooow. So many people.

They all look happy!
12:
The holidays are nearly upon us.
Take a look at the square.
16:
See the trees decked with golden
tinsel? And the big one crowned
with a star? We had a similar festival
in my world.
20:
Such a nice tree! It likes everybody
here too!
25: You can hear the tree's voice?
27:
Hmm... Normally trees don't talk, but
this one's listened a lot!
29:
They're faint, but I can hear the
voices it's heard. Happy voices,
lonely sighs... and lots of laughter!
It's a tree full of memories!
31:
In a few hundred years, it'll be able
to speak for itself.
35:
Th-that's a fascinating bit of arbor
lore...

It's a pity. I'd have loved to speak to
this tree.
38:
I guess that means I'm this tree's big
sister.
46: That's why I'm gonna do it!
47:
I'm gonna become a holiday tree
too!
54:
What... What are you doing there,
Challua?
58: She says she's a holiday tree.
63:
...She's been at it for a while now. I
don't wish to naysay her, especially
as she has her heart set on it, but I
can't say I understand.
68:
I'm a tree right now, so I'm staying
nice and still.
69:
I am thirsty, though. Could I have
some water?
74:
Certainly. And while we're at it, we
will decorate your boughs.
77:
You've made me a very happy
Challua... I mean tree.
82:
Um... Okay...

I'm sure it can't hurt to humor her for
a while.
88:
Wind, stars, voices, light... I think I'm
ready to transform!
102:
So pretty... You look incredible. Is
that really you, Challua?
110:
Still, she's right. The holiday
trimmings really suit you!
117: Hehe. Aww, you're making me blush.
121:
Now that my boughs are decked, I'm
off!
133:
*gulp* Ahh... Nothing like a warm
mug of tea on a cold winter's night.
134:
Och, but the year's gone by so fast. I
suppose when you get to be my
age, time passes in a blink,
ho-ho-ho...
142:
Gwuh?!

Wh-what's all this hullabaloo now?
144:
Do my eye sockets deceive me or is
that you, Challua? You look
positively festive!
148:
I'm a holiday tree! The others helped
decorate me!
154:
Well, well, you do make for a
splendid tree...

Ack, this won't do! This won't do at
all! The tears flow more readily as
you get older.
158: But you don't have eyes, Regitare!
162:
I've still got emotions, lass! And right
now, they're overflowing and leakin'
through me eye sockets!
163:
But aye, it's good to know that the
blessed stars are celebrated outside
of the forest as well.
166:
Everyone was having so much fun!
Do you want to come too, Regitare?
169:
Ah, I'd best not Challua. This isn't the
right holiday for the walking dead to
be out and about, ye know.
172: It'll be fine! You just have to cosplay!
176:
Hmph. It seems they've been
teaching you more of their odd
words. Ye really think I should go?
